# <type>[<scope>): <subject>
#
# - Limit to 50 characters                MAX -->|
# - Separate from body with a blank line
# - Capitalize; no ending period; use imperative mood
#
# Imperative mood? “If applied, my commit will <insert subject ...>”

# <body>
#
# - Wrap at 72 characters                                       MAX -->|
# - Explain WHAT and WHY not HOW; fine to be detailed
# - Separate paragraphs with blank lines
# - Use "-" for bullet points

# [<trailers>]
#   Link related JIRA tickets/articles (git-interpret-trailers format)
#
#   Examples: Issues: ADT-12345, ADT-78910

# Type options:
# - feat     new features
# - fix      bug fixes
# - refactor code changes that neither fix bugs nor add features
# - style    formatting changes; white-space, indentation, etc
# - docs     documentation changes
# - test     adding, updating or correcting tests
# - chore    non-production code changes, grunt tasks, etc
# - perf     performance improvements
# - revert   revert commits
# - ci       CI config and script changes
# - build    build system or dependency changes

# How to Write a Git Commit Message:
#   https://cbea.ms/git-commit/
#   https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#summary
